name: The Silent Patient
author: Alex Michaelides
notes: This book was SO good! I think I could've pieced it all together by the end but I was reading it very absent mindedly I guess. It was very thoughtfully written- the gut wrenching ending OMG.

name: Legendary
author: Stephanie Garber
notes: I definitely liked this part more than part one- though, I must appreciate the world building done in Caraval that made this one such a good read! I am really intrigued by Jacks.

notes: Definitely a fun read :) Would read it again!

name: The Final Gambit
author: Jennifer Lynn Barnes
notes: What a cozy ending! I could see myself hosting a similar quest for fun if I were a Billionare.

name: The Diary of a Young Girl
author: Anne Frank
notes: Anne's diary is definitely one of my top reads this year! So emotional and encouraging, yet sad. Anne would've changed the world- she inspires me today to embrace my humanity and myself.

name: Twilight
author: Stephenie Meyer
notes: This is so trashy that I liked it. It wass fun listening to it while I practiced my painting- would highly recommend.

name: New Moon
author: Stephenie Meyer
notes: Its become a routine- painting while Stephenie's book plays in the background- perfect way to spend an evening.

name: The Song of Achilles
author: Madeline Miller
notes: One of the best romances I've read all year. Also, I really want to dig deeper into Greek Mythology and the whole shazaam! Did you know that Alexander the Great idolised Achilles? He even believed that he was half god hiself. Can't wait to get my hands on another Madeline Miller book- probably Circe- I'd love to know how Odyssey is portrayed in it.

name: The Alchemist
author: Paulo Coelho
notes: To be straight- not my cup of tea. That said, I can see why people would find it inspirational. I still don't understand why the book was named 'The Alchemist'?? I'm guessing there's some deeper meaning - as every chapter in this book does. I just can't get myself to ponder too much about it. Overall, it was okay. One thing I'd carry forward is how he mentions something along the line 'the whole universe it rooting for you whether you believe it or not'.
